{"name": "trx-viewer", "metadata": {"name": "trx-viewer", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pyside6"], "summary": "A helper program for reading .NET test files (TRX)", "upload_time": 1735424224}, "documentation": ["# TRX Viewer\n\n<img src=\"trx_viewer/ViewerGUI/logo.svg\" alt=\"TRX VIewer logo\" style=\"width:200px;\"/>\n\nTRX Viewer is a multi-platform software for viewing .NET test (TRX) files.\nIt is highly performant, and can handle TRX files with hundreds of thousands of tests.\n\nUsers can see and filter individual tests based on test parameters such as outcome and duration, and can see specific test information such as the stdout and stderr values of selected tests.\n\n## Installation\n\nTRX viewer is available on pip:\n\n```bash\npipx install trx-viewer\n```\n\nCurrently no standalone application launcher is provided, so simply start it from the terminal.\n\n## Program Showcase\n\n![App screenshot regular](Screenshots/regular.png)\n![App screenshot filter success](Screenshots/filter_success.png)\n![App screenshot empty app](Screenshots/empty_app.png)\n![App screenshot about open](Screenshots/about_open.png)"], "modules": [{"name": "trx_viewer.trx_viewer", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "trx_viewer.trx_viewer.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "trx_viewer.__main__", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "trx_viewer.expression_filter", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "trx_viewer.expression_filter.split_word", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "string", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "